Citation.sTitle: Bubble temperature measurements on seven binary mixtures formed by ethylbenzene at 94.7 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Bubble temperatures at 94.7 kPa, over the entire composition range, were measured for the binary mixtures formed by ethylbenzene with acetophenone, amylalcohol, acrylonitrile, epichlorohydrin, N,N-dimethylacetamide, methylisobutylketone and 2-picoline. A Swietoslawski-type ebulliometer was used for the measurements. The liquid phase mole fraction versus temperature measurements were represented by the Wilson model.
